    "When the current job has finished, the pilot resumes the listening mode, waiting for another payload.",
    "• The pilot is user (\"experiment\") independent with the user code stored in plugins.-The plugins encapsulate all the code that is relevant for each pilot user.",
    "-Plugins currently exist for the ATLAS, sPHENIX and Vera C. Rubin experiments.",
    "-A joining VO can add their code specifics (e.g.",
    "how the payload and other tools should be executed, special checks and algorithms) starting from a generic plugin -Fully implemented pilot plugins range from 1,700 to over 8,000 lines of code (the generic plugin has 1,200 lines of code)."
